01:07:07.190 --> 01:07:08.356
I have a question for Sarah.

01:07:08.356 --> 01:07:11.960
You identified yourself as
someone who had left the GOP.

01:07:11.960 --> 01:07:14.240
And certainly a lot of
people have done that.

01:07:14.240 --> 01:07:17.376
And I'm wondering
how that impacts

01:07:17.376 --> 01:07:19.250
how we should understand
a lot of the numbers

01:07:19.250 --> 01:07:21.710
that we see when we see a poll
that shows a high approval

01:07:21.710 --> 01:07:24.050
rating among
Republicans for Trump.

01:07:24.050 --> 01:07:26.330
Should we be thinking,
right, but pollsters

01:07:26.330 --> 01:07:28.130
are talking to people
who don't identify

01:07:28.130 --> 01:07:31.280
as Republicans anymore, and that
should impact how we understand

01:07:31.280 --> 01:07:34.130
the number, or do
we have more people

01:07:34.130 --> 01:07:36.320
who didn't identify as
Republicans before who

01:07:36.320 --> 01:07:38.960
now do because they're from the
far-right, or they're populist,

01:07:38.960 --> 01:07:40.899
and that pulls
them into the GOP?

01:07:40.899 --> 01:07:42.940
And I don't know if that
balances out in any way.

01:07:42.940 --> 01:07:44.090
I just don't know
what to make of it.

01:07:44.090 --> 01:07:46.572
- So of the numbers that
I presented in particular?

01:07:46.572 --> 01:07:47.900
Or--

01:07:47.900 --> 01:07:49.400
- I'm just--

01:07:49.400 --> 01:07:50.900
- Are you talking
about, in general,

01:07:50.900 --> 01:07:52.635
Trump's approval rating
among Republicans,

01:07:52.635 --> 01:07:52.940
how accurate is that?

01:07:52.940 --> 01:07:53.439
- Yes.

01:07:53.439 --> 01:07:57.920
But any other numbers about
Republican feelings about x.

01:07:57.920 --> 01:08:00.760
I'm wondering if we have
to say, well, that's not--

01:08:00.760 --> 01:08:03.800
- Is it really reflective
of the Republican Party,

01:08:03.800 --> 01:08:06.270
and conservatives, and
the Trumpification--

01:08:06.270 --> 01:08:10.970
because there is
that new GOP base,

01:08:10.970 --> 01:08:13.470
which I don't feel like is
reflective of the Republican

01:08:13.470 --> 01:08:14.060
Party.

01:08:14.060 --> 01:08:16.939
My parents still
identify as Republicans.

01:08:16.939 --> 01:08:19.260
They don't like Donald Trump.

01:08:19.260 --> 01:08:21.620
So the numbers are
tough, but I think--

01:08:21.620 --> 01:08:24.149
they're tough with
the approval rating.

01:08:24.149 --> 01:08:27.359
But the approval rating numbers
that I gave were nationwide.

01:08:27.359 --> 01:08:29.620
The 41% to the 43%.

01:08:29.620 --> 01:08:31.819
So I think some people--

01:08:31.819 --> 01:08:35.630
and I think this is true
of the 2016 election--

01:08:35.630 --> 01:08:37.910
are quietly approving what
he's doing, and may not

01:08:37.910 --> 01:08:41.720
be identifying that to you and
me as people, but are saying,

01:08:41.720 --> 01:08:44.779
the economy's fine.

01:08:44.779 --> 01:08:47.359
Brett Kavanaugh
just got nominated--

01:08:47.359 --> 01:08:50.769
so I think there's
a quiet acceptance.

01:08:50.769 --> 01:08:52.130
Does that makes sense?

01:08:52.130 --> 01:08:52.869
- Yeah.

01:08:52.869 --> 01:08:53.369
- Sadly.

01:08:53.369 --> 01:08:53.910
- I think so.

01:08:53.910 --> 01:08:54.529
Yeah.

01:08:54.529 --> 01:08:55.520
Thank you, thank you.

01:08:55.520 --> 01:08:56.728
- It's not satisfying, is it?

01:08:56.728 --> 01:08:57.670
- No.

01:08:57.670 --> 01:08:58.211
Yeah, I know.

01:08:58.211 --> 01:09:00.388
[CHUCKLING]

