01:13:24.514 --> 01:13:26.680
is different from Tejanos,
different from Mexicanos,

01:13:26.680 --> 01:13:29.410
different from people from
Colombia or Central America.

01:13:29.410 --> 01:13:30.320
It's different.

01:13:30.320 --> 01:13:31.720
Dominicans.

01:13:31.720 --> 01:13:33.850
So there's no monolith.

01:13:33.850 --> 01:13:36.520
And before Trump
came along, the GOP

01:13:36.520 --> 01:13:39.760
was actually making some
significant inroads,

01:13:39.760 --> 01:13:42.730
and had funded
programs where we had

01:13:42.730 --> 01:13:45.940
people in the center of
the highest population--

01:13:45.940 --> 01:13:48.170
Latinos in Texas,
and in Arizona,

01:13:48.170 --> 01:13:49.930
New Mexico, and
California-- where

01:13:49.930 --> 01:13:53.470
they were running voter
engagement, because every day,

01:13:53.470 --> 01:13:57.400
in California, 7,000 Latinos
become eligible to vote.

01:13:57.400 --> 01:13:58.420
18-year-olds.

01:13:58.420 --> 01:14:03.420
It's a number that the GOP, at
one point, was deeply invested

01:14:03.420 --> 01:14:04.480
and speaking to.

01:14:04.480 --> 01:14:06.760
And then Trump came along.

01:14:06.760 --> 01:14:08.350
And Trump messed up--

01:14:08.350 --> 01:14:09.790
despite what
happened in Florida,

01:14:09.790 --> 01:14:15.790
Trump messed up the GOP plans
to really engage and bring it.

01:14:15.790 --> 01:14:20.710
So in Florida specifically,
the GOP has won by 1%.

01:14:20.710 --> 01:14:22.870
1%.

01:14:22.870 --> 01:14:26.470
Out of 15 million voters,
it's such a small number.

01:14:26.470 --> 01:14:29.056
And that number,
although Andrew Gillum--

01:14:29.056 --> 01:14:30.430
who's a gubernatorial
candidate--

01:14:30.430 --> 01:14:32.763
wasn't able to overcome that,
the Democrats weren't able

01:14:32.763 --> 01:14:35.380
to overcome that, there
are efforts on the ground--

01:14:35.380 --> 01:14:38.350
I mentioned Andrea Mercado
from an organization

01:14:38.350 --> 01:14:40.910
called the New Florida Majority.

01:14:40.910 --> 01:14:44.620
And that is not a one-and-done
type of organization.

01:14:44.620 --> 01:14:46.510
It's a statewide
organization that

01:14:46.510 --> 01:14:49.900
continues to build and
outreach among the Latinx

01:14:49.900 --> 01:14:51.250
and black communities.

01:14:51.250 --> 01:14:53.680
And the gains that
they saw in terms

01:14:53.680 --> 01:14:56.995
of turnout and engagement,
if they're fully funded

01:14:56.995 --> 01:14:59.500
and continue on
this path, you're

01:14:59.500 --> 01:15:04.940
going to see even stronger
Latinx turnout come 2020.

01:15:04.940 --> 01:15:06.190
- The only thing I would add--

01:15:06.190 --> 01:15:07.231
I agree with all of that.

01:15:07.231 --> 01:15:10.922
And I would just add that
the new American majority--

01:15:10.922 --> 01:15:12.880
as well, I would say
Asian-Americans-- are also

01:15:12.880 --> 01:15:16.420
a slightly more complicated
demographic in-group in terms

01:15:16.420 --> 01:15:18.460
of its voter preference.

01:15:18.460 --> 01:15:21.760
So there are absolutely
important distinctions,

01:15:21.760 --> 01:15:25.930
and differences, and values,
and political leanings

01:15:25.930 --> 01:15:27.610
within that new
American majority

01:15:27.610 --> 01:15:30.587
that politicians who
are emerging to lead it

01:15:30.587 --> 01:15:32.420
are going to have to
be paying attention to.

01:15:32.420 --> 01:15:34.390
So that's-- I think I'm just
reiterating, essentially,

01:15:34.390 --> 01:15:35.420
what you said, but.

01:15:35.420 --> 01:15:36.781
- Yeah.

01:15:36.781 --> 01:15:37.280
- Hi.

01:15:37.280 --> 01:15:39.710
My name's David Layman,
member of the general public.

01:15:39.710 --> 01:15:40.964
[CHUCKLING]

01:15:40.964 --> 01:15:41.880
- That's a good title.

01:15:41.880 --> 01:15:45.290
- No affiliation with Harvard.

