01:16:52.124 --> 01:16:53.640
Pollsters had no idea.

01:16:53.640 --> 01:16:56.000
So what the pollsters
we work with,

01:16:56.000 --> 01:16:57.500
like Celinda Lake and PPP--

01:16:57.500 --> 01:16:59.450
these are Democratic
Party pollsters--

01:16:59.450 --> 01:17:02.750
they have to change
their strategy

01:17:02.750 --> 01:17:07.040
to be able to figure out
what's really going on.

01:17:07.040 --> 01:17:09.890
If they're doing
calling, for example--

01:17:09.890 --> 01:17:11.960
people don't have home phones.

01:17:11.960 --> 01:17:14.180
Just the methodology
in that in order

01:17:14.180 --> 01:17:17.700
to figure out what voters
think has to change.

01:17:17.700 --> 01:17:21.530
And that five-out-of-five-- what
they call the regular voters--

01:17:21.530 --> 01:17:24.050
they're going to have to
expand who they ask for.

01:17:24.050 --> 01:17:26.112
These are eligible,
maybe registered.

01:17:26.112 --> 01:17:28.070
Maybe they've never voted
for president before.

01:17:28.070 --> 01:17:30.150
They need to ask
that person too.

01:17:30.150 --> 01:17:33.770
And in particular races,
and districts and states,

01:17:33.770 --> 01:17:37.070
they need to prioritize,
particularly what

01:17:37.070 --> 01:17:39.410
women of color are doing
on the Democratic side,

01:17:39.410 --> 01:17:42.740
because that's an indicator
of how, in the primaries,

01:17:42.740 --> 01:17:44.350
things will go.

01:17:44.350 --> 01:17:46.760
- I'm going to jump in
on this one too, since--

01:17:46.760 --> 01:17:50.151
I study public opinion, so I
use polling data quite a bit.

01:17:50.151 --> 01:17:51.650
But I think it's
safe to say there's

01:17:51.650 --> 01:17:55.280
a vast over-reliance on
polls as a measure of what

01:17:55.280 --> 01:17:56.840
public opinion is.

01:17:56.840 --> 01:18:00.530
And it's our best-known
way of capturing

01:18:00.530 --> 01:18:03.620
what a broad population
thinks at a moment in time.

01:18:03.620 --> 01:18:06.530
But I think 2016--

01:18:06.530 --> 01:18:08.450
I don't think it was as
much of a wake-up call

01:18:08.450 --> 01:18:11.720
as it should have been, but
it was a wake-up call to say,

01:18:11.720 --> 01:18:13.430
public opinion is
complex, and there's

01:18:13.430 --> 01:18:15.650
a lot that's going on
that we don't understand,

01:18:15.650 --> 01:18:19.458
and our current methods
aren't adequate for the task.

01:18:19.458 --> 01:18:20.850
- Thank you very much.

01:18:23.531 --> 01:18:24.030
- Hi.

01:18:24.030 --> 01:18:25.700
Tom [INAUDIBLE].

01:18:25.700 --> 01:18:28.490
